The paper discusses the use of evolutionary robotics to synthesize machines with animal-like abilities, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also introduces a new concept, evolvability signatures, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of neural networks and pattern generators in the study could also make it relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the study involves the adaptation of robots to changes in fitness, which could be relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
